Welcome to 247AUTORENT! We are a trusted host on Turo.
-Call  for booking support and question please call 702-703-4599

Below are some of the instructions and pieces of information you need to know about us and our rental.

1.) ID verification: Two photos will be requested: your valid driver's license photo and your selfie photo holding your driver's license. If you don't have it, it's expired, or you don’t feel comfortable providing it, you are unable to book.

2.) We are open 24/7; we have your time covered for morning or night pick-up and drop-off.

3.) We have a delivery service to your location or airport, but take note that this service is not free. Just choose delivery and input the location where you want us to drop off the car.

4.) Got a flat tire and a dead battery during the trip? No worries. Call Turo roadside assistance at +1 415 965 4525.

5.) Need extras? We offer baby and booster seats, prepaid fuel, one-way trips (SAN-AZ-LAS), camping tents, etc.

6.) NO PETS, NO SMOKING, OR VAPING: No smoking or pets are allowed in the vehicles. (Other renters might be allergic.) Absolutely no tobacco, marijuana, liquid, etc. smoking or vaping in the vehicle. Violators will be pursued for up to the full extent of Turo's $250 smoking fine. We are forced to utilize professional ozone decontamination when this occurs.

7.) GAS MUST BE REFILLED: Gas must be refilled back to the same level that you picked up. If you are in a hurry, do not refill the gas. We will charge a pro-rated amount of gas plus a $10 convenience fee. No hard feelings whatsoever. So the gas might not be full when you pick it up because the previous guest didn't fill it up. Just return it to the same level.

8.) Any TOLL ROAD citation or PARKING citation will be requested. Please pay the TOLL or any parking ticket if you received any! Otherwise, it will be your responsibility to pay any kind of extra fee.

We always do our best to give you a great experience with us; if you feel it, please leave a 5-star review. If the rent experience was less than satisfactory, please let us know as soon as possible so we have the opportunity to make it right.

My hobbies are not as excited as many other people. Everything from how the body moves and how it should move biomechanically for each individual is absolutely striking to me. 

This leads me to why I have decided to pop onto Turo as not only a way to get connected with the car lovers of the world, but to learn more on how to properly make extra income on the side in order to pay for my upcoming Doctorate’s of Physical Therapy program. I know going on a car app is such an oddball and random approach compared to everything I have been involved in but hey, it sounds like fun.
